,Recommended,256370,9750564,"Posted: 6 April, 2014",all,Teddy,"This is a really awesome game. It can appeal to those who really race and appreciate the physics of the realistic mode more, or those who just like to play a fun racing game. If you are wondering how this compares to other off road racing games, particularly MX vs ATV, this is how:-MXGP has really good physics and is less arcady than MX vs ATV (especially when you are on the realistic mode)-MXGP gives you option to set up your bike however you choose. This will probably appeal to those who really race or know a thing or two about it.-MXGP has a more realistic career mode, letting you choose a team to sign with and wearing your endorsments on your jersey and bike.-MXGP features all real brands, people, and tracks, unlike MX vs ATV (MX vs ATV only has KTM available as a real brand for dirt bikes)Those are just a few of the ways MXGP beats MX vs ATV. As far as the graphics and sound go, I'd say both games are pretty good there. MXGP does have nice graphics, but the animation at the end of the race when you win is just... unnatural.MX vs ATV give you more things to do, being a game that doesn't only focus on dirt bikes (even though that was probably their main focus).MX vs ATV lets you drive a bunch of other different vehicles like an ATV, trophy truck, and more. MX vs ATV also features more types of racing. It features supercross, motocross, enduro, and has free ride available.Things I wish were included in this game:-Free ride-Enduro-Hard Enduro-Multiplayer for each of those thingsOverall, MXGP is a great game for motocross enthusiasts and your average gamer alike. As for which of the two games mentioned are better, that depends entirely on you and the features/style of offroad racing game you want. MX vs ATV supercross is planned and hopefully supercross isnt the only style of racing they include because that is one thing that I do love about Reflex (the amount of racing styles available).Another thing is that MX vs ATV might beat MXGP with the real time ground deformation, but both games do it well."
