,Recommended,256370,9701037,"Posted: 1 April, 2014",all,69th_Zeb,"The RBR of motocross:I wasn't all that impressed with Milestone's WRC series, but having raced, collided and wiped out in real life, this one blew me away.My pros:-Bikes generate ruts, and the track changes during the race.-Independent center of gravities for bike/rider and independent wheel physics...During a wheelie, you can push a wheel down on a high speed turning woop and turn slightly (great one at the start of Si Racha).-Landing sideways or preloading the suspension on a slide will snap the bike back and forth to the point where the rider gets thrown over the bike (nice!).-If you're scrapping to clear a double you can bunny hop some to help clear a gap.-Track friction and berms make sense.Cons:-Takes a few hours to make the controls feel like a bike. It's just part of the deal though. Not really a complaint.-Scenery a bit dull for today's graphics, but bikes look great.-Scrubs felt a bit baked, but it's alright.With a few tweaks, making an enduro/Dakar/Romaniacs out of this game would be fantastic (even if it was one race). A separate game for Trials would also be pretty cool. I think these guys could pull it off."
