76561198047686869,Recommended,256370,14831451,"Posted: 10 March, 2015",all,Hannibal802,"Played the demo of this game, and thought it was kinda meh. Wasn't something I really thought I'd enjoy. Few months later I'm writing this review because I was wrong. This game is a sleeper. The career mode is top notch, you start out in MX2 and have to race your way to the best teams in MX2 and then work your way through MX1. The ground physics are amazing, the air physics need some work, but ground physics make up for the lack of feeling in the air. The AI is pretty good, they are really hard when you let them get infront of you, its a challenege to catch them, but once you are in 1st, you can walk away pretty easy. I heard there is a mod to make the AI stronger, I plan on doing that soon."
76561198115301175,Recommended,256370,14832688,"Posted: 10 March, 2015",all,Calibreus,"The game is really fun! Physics are actually suprisingly great and when the AI is set to realistic; it gives you a challenge (unlike some other motocross games). The bikes look great and so do the riders. I also really like the replay feature (although the ability to rewind would be nice).However, the game acts like it's in Beta. There are many crashes and glitches. And the landscape and overall graphics are pretty terrible for a game made in 2014 (other than the bikes and riders as I mentioned before). The bikes also sound like total crap. There are also only 14 tracks, no free roam (which is understandable for MXGP, but there should be more tracks), very restricted customization, lack of various in-game social feed responses, and so forth.Now it may seem like this game is outweighed with con's from my review, but if you are tolerant enough to look past these faults; it's actually a pretty good game. The gameplay is really great and I like the idea of being in different teams and having different sponsors (although you cannot choose your sponsors). I also really appreciate having actual bikes and not having to pay money for DLC that allows me to ride a Honda or a Yamaha.Overall, I think this game is worth it for anyone that rides motocross or dirt bikes in real life (or perhaps just really like motocross games). But don't expect a complete game, there is a lot that needs to be fixed/added."
