,Recommended,256370,9795854,"Posted: 12 April, 2014",all,OsamabinFetus,"When trying to compare this game to similar competitors, it's clear who the winner is. This game has amazing graphics, physics, and sound compared to any other game of its kind. Although the ruts don't really do anything, and the revs die mid air, and there's no real mid air movement, it's easily better than any other MX game. What's disappointing is that the game consists of many different 4 strokes, but not a single 2 stroke. Fair enough that during the 2013 MXGP season there weren't any 2 strokes competing, but you've still got to give people the option to ride one. Maybe during rider customisation there could be a choice to make your own bike, and that's where the 2 stroke could come in, but we don't even have the option for that. The game gives many hours of gameplay, online and offline, and there's many different tracks and bikes to choose from. The game has full controller support (thank god), as it would be impossible to play without one. Overall, I'm pretty impressed. All I want to see is 2 strokes, and some DLC, and it would make the game one of my favourite games to this day. A few bugs to be fixed, but like every new game you need to give the developers time to fix them."
