,Recommended,256370,30305593,Posted: 3 March,all,Gergor,"The first time I played this I didn't care for it - it felt ridiculously hard and like the rider was eating it for no discernible reason. But I gave it another shot and paid more attention to what I was doing, and as I started to get the hang of it I found it increasingly rewarding. Over the course of a few race weekends in career mode I moved the difficulty up from Easy all the way to Realistic (max). I'm still playing with semi-auto rider controls because I just don't care that much, but it's fun.There is quite a bit of variety in the tracks, both in their layouts (flat, very hilly, fast or technical, and so on) and in the surface. I came across tracks where I could not get a decent lap time until I changed things in the bike set-up, which speaks well for that. The surface of the track in this can look kind of janky at times (frequently the ruts don't render until they're behind you) and the engine sounds could be a lot better, but I'm really enjoying it and I think it's very much worth buying on sale.Previous MX games I've played were MX vs ATV Alive & Reflex."
